  <recipe id="Chocolate Fudge Cookies">
    <head>
      <title>Chocolate Fudge Cookies</title>
      <source>Karen Tedesco</source>
      <categories>
        <cat class="main">Cookies</cat>
        <cat class="region">America</cat>
				<cat class="diet">Nut-free</cat>
      </categories>
    </head>
    <description><xhtml:p>These are delicious, fudgy chocolate cookies! I first tasted them at a friend's house during a holiday gathering of teachers. We always eat well when we get together and often have recipes available for anyone who is interested.</xhtml:p></description>
    <ingredients system="US">
      <ing-div>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1/2</qty>
            <unit>cup</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>vegetable oil</item>
<!--1/2 cup vegetable oil-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>4</qty>
            <unit>ounces</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>chocolate, melted</item>
<!--4 squares melted chocolate(12 tablespoons cocoa+ 4 tablespoons butter)-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>2</qty>
            <unit>cup</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>granulated sugar</item>
<!--2 cups granulated sugar-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>4</qty>
          </amt>
          <item>eggs</item>
<!--4 eggs-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>2</qty>
            <unit>teaspoons</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>vanilla</item>
<!--2 teaspoons vanilla-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1/2</qty>
            <unit>teaspoon</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>salt</item>
<!--1/2 teaspoon salt-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>2</qty>
            <unit>cup</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>flour</item>
<!--2 cups flour-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>2</qty>
            <unit>teaspoons baking</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>powder</item>
<!--2 teaspoons baking powder-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <item>chocolate nonpariel candies</item>
<!--chocolate nonpariel candies-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <item>powdered sugar</item>
<!--powdered sugar-->
        </ing>
      </ing-div>
    </ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>Mix the oil, chocolate and sugar until well blended. Add one egg at a time to this mixture. Mix well and add the vanilla. Sift the flour, salt and baking powder and add to the chocolate mixture.</step>
      <step>Chill the dough for several hours or overnight. Drop 1 teaspoon of the dough into the powdered sugar. Roll it around and form a ball. Place these rounded shapes on a greased cookie sheet and bake for about 10 minutes at <temp><qty>350</qty><tempunit unit="F" system="US">degrees</tempunit><!--350  degrees--></temp>.</step>
      <step>Remove cookie sheet from the oven, and place a nonpariel candy into the center of each of the hot cookies. Remove them from the cookie sheet and cool completely on a rack.</step>
    </directions>
  </recipe>
